Sublime

> Package control
	> install this to allow your sublime to access a bunch 
		of useful packages on the internet
	> drag it into the folder that opens when you open 
		sublime text >> preferences >> browse packages

> color sublime has a package that you can install to change
	themes
	> packages constrol > search for install package > search for color sublime
	> bittersweet

> clang complete: package that tells you when your code does not
	pass the debuggin checks.  It updates every time that you
	save.
	> package manager > install package > clang-complete
	https://packagecontrol.io/packages/Clang-Complete

> sublime console: 
	open: ctrl + `

> header: search sublime 42 header
